cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.LG

The paper deals with the problem of pupil detection in eye-tracking, which is a common application in computer vision and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of eye-tracking in health monitoring and driver assistance, which falls under the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The method proposed in the paper is designed to work in real-time and is integrated into an open-source software, which suggests the category of cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper also mentions the use of a confidence measure for pupil detection, which could be considered as a machine learning problem and falls under the category of cs.MM (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper presents a new dataset for evaluating pupil detection algorithms, which could be relevant to researchers working in the field of cs.LG (Learning).
